# Operations Safety

## Git

- Only create commits when the user explicitly asks
- Never run `git push --force` to `main` or `master`
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless the user explicitly requests it
- Never amend commits that are already pushed to remote

## Database

- All schema changes go through Alembic migrations — no manual production table edits
- Never run destructive commands against production Neon (`DROP`, `TRUNCATE`, mass `DELETE`) without explicit user approval
- Tests must use a separate or isolated database — never run tests against production

## Deployment & config

- Do not change Vercel, Neon, or GitHub OAuth app settings without user confirmation
- Keep local dev on Docker Compose Postgres; production uses Neon — do not conflate the two

## Scope

- Read `memory-bank/` before making architectural or behavioral changes
- Make minimal, focused diffs — do not refactor unrelated code
- Do not break the v1 API contract; v1 must stay unauthenticated and backward-compatible
